Agenda

Box Model
Display Property in CSS
Overflow in CSS
CSS Units



box Boxing : Content Box 

Total Rendered Width = content width + padding-left + padding-right + border-left + border-right

Total Rendered Height = content height + padding-top + padding-bottom + border-top + border-bottom




box Boxing : Border Box 

Total Content Width = Element  width - ( padding-left + padding-right + border-left + border-right)

Total Content Height = Element height - ( padding-top + padding-bottom + border-top + border-bottom) 








1. Absolute Units


These are fixed units and do not scale based on other elements or screen size.

px
pt
cm
mm
in

Use absolute units when you need precise physical sizes, like for print styles.



2. Relative Units


%  : any perentage relative to a parent  (Flexible layouts, widths, heights, margins)
vh,vw : relative to a screen size (Full Screen Sections , responsive layouts)
rem  : relative to the font-size of the root element (usually the <html> tag). (font sizes , spacing , padding , margin)
em : relative to the font-size of its closest parent (which may be inherited or explicitly set) (Buttons, nested components ..etc)

